snippet.textDisplay: What singers (especially in India) should learn from these great Masters - some of whom left India and migrated to Pakistan in 1947. You don't hit the stage and expect to excel after learning music for two years. It shows in the quality. At this age, it is simply her voice that is shining there. Hardly any support from orchestration. Just because the western education system gives a graduation degree in 3/4 years, the same does NOT apply to the art pursuits of the Indian sub-continent ( I wonder if it applies in the West too!). Here I think the minimum is 10 years - especially for those not fortunate enough to have grown up in a musician's family.
snippet.textOriginal: What singers (especially in India) should learn from these great Masters - some of whom left India and migrated to Pakistan in 1947. You don't hit the stage and expect to excel after learning music for two years. It shows in the quality. At this age, it is simply her voice that is shining there. Hardly any support from orchestration. Just because the western education system gives a graduation degree in 3/4 years, the same does NOT apply to the art pursuits of the Indian sub-continent ( I wonder if it applies in the West too!). Here I think the minimum is 10 years - especially for those not fortunate enough to have grown up in a musician's family.
